Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with stereo visual odometry systems and motion estimation, which are core topics in computer vision.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper's focus on visual SLAM (Simultaneous Localization and Mapping) makes it relevant to robotics.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper may involve machine learning techniques for solving the stereo relative pose problem.
4. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper's focus on visual odometry and motion estimation is a common topic in CVPR.
5. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper may involve graphics techniques for visualizing the results of the stereo relative pose estimation.
